Ban/measure is in effect in all subnational jurisdictions
The legislation does not allow designated smoking rooms except if the health authority allows them by administrative act. Until now, no such administrative act has been made.
However the Minister may allow a person to smoke in a non-smoking area.
Separate, completely enclosed smoking rooms are allowed under very strict conditions.  Refer to WHO Report on the Global Tobacco Epidemic, 2015, Technical Note I for more information.
